# CCNA conventions

## Content & AI

- **Curated-first** on Study/Practice — no live AI fetch on page load for free users
- AI generation is **premium-only** (`premiumFeatures.js`); bundled flashcards/diagrams/quizzes stay free
- Prefer patches in `contentEnrichmentPatches.js` / `factoryTrapPatches.js` over editing giant curated files inline

## Code placement

- New UI: `src/components/` or `src/lab/` or `src/tabs/` — not new 100+ line blocks in `App.jsx`
- CLI/labs: `src/lab/cliEngine.js` + `CiscoTerminal.jsx`
- Responsive CSS: `src/ui/appShell.js` classes over one-off inline widths

## Mobile

Mental-check: iPhone 390×844, landscape 844×390, iPad, MacBook. Use `dvh`, safe areas, `ccna-h-scroll` for horizontal carousels.

## Forbidden without explicit user ask

- `src/ui/appTheme.js` token changes
- Hash routing / view state machine in `App.jsx`
- `.env*` or secrets
- Commits or deploy (unless c&d / ship it)

See `ai-improvement-logs/DO_NOT_TOUCH.md`.
